local LORE = {
  "The Emperor of Mankind sits upon the Golden Throne, an undying carcass powered by a thousand psychic sacrifices daily, serving as the Imperium's literal and spiritual battery.",
  "Space Marines, or Adeptus Astartes, are bio-engineered super-soldiers, organized into Chapters of roughly a thousand warriors, each sworn to protect the Emperor.",
  "The Imperial Guard, now the Astra Militarum, is the Imperium's primary fighting force, composed of trillions of regular human soldiers levied from countless worlds.",
  "Inquisitors are the Emperor's secret police, wielding near-absolute power to root out heresy, corruption, and the alien threat across the galaxy.",
  "The Adeptus Mechanicus are the machine-worshippers of Mars, who maintain the Imperium's technology and believe all knowledge is contained in the Omnissiah.",
  "The Ecclesiarchy, or the Adeptus Ministorum, is the official state church, spreading the Imperial Creed that venerates the Emperor as a god.",
  "The Administratum is the unimaginably vast bureaucracy of the Imperium, notorious for its inefficiency and endless mountains of parchment.",
  "Hive Worlds are colossal, densely populated planets where billions of humans live in stratified, mile-high cities, never seeing the natural sun.",
  "Navigators are sanctioned mutants with a third eye that allows them to perceive the currents of the Warp, making interstellar travel possible.",
  "The Astropathic Choir is a massive network of psychers who mentally scream across light-years to transmit messages, often driving them insane.",
  "Bolters are the standard armament of a Space Marine, firing mass-reactive explosive shells that shred unarmored foes.",
  "The High Lords of Terra are the twelve unelected officials who rule the Imperium in the Emperor's name, often locked in centuries-long power struggles.",
  "Venerable Dreadnoughts are once-mortally-wounded heroes encased in sarcophagi within powerful war machines, kept alive for centuries to continue fighting.",
  "An Exterminatus is the complete destruction of a planet's biosphere or population, a drastic measure used to prevent the spread of irreparable corruption or contagion.",
  "The Black Templars maintain that the Codex Astartes is merely a suggestion, and they wage eternal crusades with no home-world, seeking battle across the stars.",
  "Chaos is the corrupting influence of the Warp, born from the sentient emotions of mortals and manifested through the four great Chaos Gods.",
  "Khorne, the Blood God, embodies violence, murder, and rage, caring only from the spilling of blood, regardless of whose.",
  "Tzeentch, the Changer of Ways, is the master of ambition, conspiracy, and evolution, whose plans are infinitely complex and often contradictory.",
  "Nurgle, the Plague Lord, is the god of entropy, disease, and despair, who offers his followers a perverse form of morbid contentment.",
  "Slaanesh, the Dark Prince, is the god of excess, pleasure, and obsession, born from the psychic culmination of the ancient Eldar empire's depravity.",
  "Chaos Space Marines are the Traitor Legions and their descendants, who turned against the Emperor during the Horus Heresy ten millennia ago.",
  "The Eye of Terror is a massive, permanent Warp rift in space, serving as the corrupted home-base for the largest concentrations of Chaos forces.",
  "A Daemon is a psychic entity and manifestation of a Chaos God, a being of pure Warp-stuff that can possess mortal bodies.",
  "Warbands of Chaos Space Marines constantly launch Black Crusades into Imperial territory, seeking plunder, power, or simply to spread carnage.",
  "Possessed Marines have willingly allowed a Daemon to merge with their bodies, gaining horrific mutations and great power at the cost of their sanity.",
  "Fabius Bile, the Clonelord, is a mad scientist of the Chaos Space Marines who creates monstrous Astartes variants and clones the Primarchs for his dark experiments.",
  "The Iron Warriors specialize in siege warfare, preferring to grind their enemies down with overwhelming artillery and fortifications.",
  "Word Bearers are the first and most zealous of the Traitor Legions, viewing the Chaos Gods as true deities to be worshipped and obeyed.",
  "Daemon Worlds are planets so utterly warped by Chaos that the natural laws of reality break down, forming living, mutable hellscapes.",
  "The Great Rift, a massive warp storm, tore the galaxy in half and plunged the Imperium Nihilus into an age of perpetual darkness and terror.",
  "The Orks are a vast, green-skinned, fungal species whose very existence and technology are governed by a psychic field called WAAAGH!, which makes things work simply because they believe they will.",
  "An Ork Warlord will eventually attract enough other Orks to form a massive WAAAGH!, a migratory crusade of destruction that consumes solar systems.",
  "The Orks' simple mentality means they find fighting to be the greatest pleasure, and they see constant warfare as a joyous form of existence.",
  "The Eldar, or Aeldari, are a dwindling, ancient race, once masters of the galaxy, whose hubris birthed Slaanesh and led to the near-total destruction of their civilization.",
  "Craftworlds are colossal, sentient, space-faring vessels that house the surviving Eldar, travelling the galaxy on carefully calculated courses to avoid detection.",
  "Farseers are the most powerful Eldar psykers, who use complex divinations to navigate the future and guide their people along the Path of the Seer.",
  "The Dark Eldar, or Drukhari, are depraved corsairs from the dark city of Commorragh who stave off the slow psychic draining of Slaanesh by inflicting pain on others.",
  "The Tyranids are an extragalactic super-organism, a terrifying swarm driven by the collective Hive Mind with the sole purpose of consuming all biomass in the galaxy.",
  "The Shadow in the Warp is the psychic pall cast by the Hive Fleet that dampens and eventually cuts off all psychic communication and activity, including the Astronomican.",
  "A Genestealer Cult is a clandestine, multi-generational xenos infestation that secretly takes root on Imperial worlds, preparing the populace for the arrival of the main Tyranid fleet.",
  "The T'au Empire is a young, rapidly expanding civilization driven by the concept of the Greater Good, utilizing advanced technology and coordinated combined arms warfare.",
  "The T'au rely heavily on their robotic Battlesuits, such as the agile Crisis Suits and the towering Riptides, for heavy combat.",
  "The Necrons are a race of ancient, skeletal robotic warriors who willingly transferred their consciousness into living metal bodies, a process that cost them their souls.",
  "Tomb Worlds are Necron planets where the entire population lies in silent stasis, waiting for a signal to awaken and reclaim their former galactic empire.",
  "C'tan, or Star Gods, are powerful entities of pure energy who were tricked by the Necrons into becoming bound to their living metal bodies.",
  "The Ork's ability to collectively believe things makes them incredibly dangerous: a red vehicle is factually faster simply because every Ork believes it is.",
  "The Jokaero are mysterious, diminutive alien orangutans whose incredible, instinctively created technology is beyond the understanding of the Mechanicus.",
  "The Kroot are a mercenary avian species who integrate the DNA of their defeated enemies by eating them, gaining their best genetic traits.",
  "The Hrud are a reclusive, nomadic xenos species whose passage can instantly and violently age their surroundings, causing rust, decay, and rapid biological senescence.",
  "The Interex was a technologically sophisticated, harmonious human and xenos alliance that was tragically destroyed during the Great Crusade due to misunderstanding and manipulation.",
  "The Great Crusade was the Emperor's 200-year-long war to reunite the scattered human worlds under the banner of the Imperium before the Horus Heresy.",
  "The Horus Heresy was a devastating galaxy-wide civil war where half of the Primarchs and their Space Marine Legions betrayed the Emperor to serve Chaos.",
  "The Primarchs were the twenty superhuman sons of the Emperor, each a master strategist and warrior, who led the original Space Marine Legions.",
  "Horus Lupercal, the Emperor's favored son and Warmaster of the Great Crusade, was the first and greatest Primarch to fall to Chaos.",
  "The Siege of Terra was the climactic battle where the Emperor finally defeated the corrupted Horus, but was mortally wounded and interred on the Golden Throne.",
  "The Burning of Prospero was the Imperial punitive action that led the psychic Thousand Sons Legion, led by Magnus the Red, into the arms of Tzeentch.",
  "The Iron Cage was the brutal, protracted siege orchestrated by Perturabo, Primarch of the Iron Warriors, as a decades-long trap to utterly break the Imperial Fists.",
  "The War in the Webway was a secret, disastrous conflict fought by the Emperor and his Custodes to carve a stable path through the dimension between the stars.",
  "The Great Scouring was the ruthless campaign of revenge and reunification waged by the loyalist Primarchs after the Heresy to cleanse the galaxy of the remaining traitors.",
  "The Codex Astartes, penned by Roboute Guilliman, decreed that the Legions be broken into smaller, more manageable Chapters to prevent future rebellions.",
  "The Age of Apostasy saw the tyrannical rule of Goge Vandire, whose cruelty was eventually ended by the forces of the Adepta Sororitas and the Imperial Guard.",
  "Abaddon the Despoiler, the Warmaster of Chaos, led twelve failed Black Crusades before the thirteenth succeeded in cracking the Imperium.",
  "The Fall of Cadia saw the destruction of the fortress world and the subsequent creation of the Great Rift, marking a turning point in galactic history.",
  "Guilliman was resurrected in the current millennium, taking the title of Lord Commander of the Imperium and instigating the Indomitus Crusade.",
  "The Beast Arises was a massive conflict against a colossal Ork WAAAGH! that shattered entire Imperial institutions and almost toppled the Imperium.",
  "The Custodes, or the Adeptus Custodes, are the Emperor's personal guard, genetically superior even to the Space Marines and clad in golden armor.",
  "The Sisters of Battle, or the Adepta Sororitas, are the all-female military arm of the Ecclesiarchy, burning heretics with righteous zeal and flamer fire.",
  "The Deathwatch is a secret, specialized Chapter composed of Space Marine veterans from across all Chapters, tasked with eliminating specific xenos threats.",
  "The Grey Knights are a mysterious, secret Chapter of Space Marines composed entirely of powerful psykers, dedicated to fighting the daemonic forces of Chaos.",
  "The Sisters of Silence are a legion of anti-psykers whose mere presence nullifies psychic powers, a rare and vital defense against the Warp.",
  "Rogue Traders are Imperial agents given Letters of Marque, granting them the right to explore and exploit the unknown regions of the galaxy for the Emperor.",
  "The Adeptus Arbites are the militarized law enforcement of the Imperium, responsible for upholding the Lex Imperialis, or Imperial law, on human worlds.",
  "Tech-Priests of the Mechanicus see all technology as sacred and perform extensive surgical and mechanical modifications to themselves in search of mechanical perfection.",
  "The Librarius is the division of a Space Marine Chapter that houses its sanctioned psykers, who channel the power of the Warp to aid their brethren.",
  "Commissars are political officers within the Astra Militarum who ensure the absolute loyalty and morale of the troops, often by summary execution for cowardice.",
  "The Warp, or Immaterium, is a parallel dimension of raw psychic energy, the source of all magic, faster-than-light travel, and daemonic entities.",
  "The Astronomican is a psychic beacon generated by the Emperor, allowing human ships to navigate the tumultuous Warp across the galactic core.",
  "Warp Travel is accomplished by plunging a ship into the Immaterium, where the journey is instantaneous but perilous, subject to daemonic attack and temporal anomalies.",
  "Heresy is the ultimate crime in the Imperium, ranging from worshiping false gods to consorting with aliens or even doubting the Emperor.",
  "Mutants are often shunned and persecuted in the Imperium, though some sanctioned variants, like the Navigators and some Astropaths, are grudgingly accepted.",
  "The Golden Age of Technology was a period millennia ago when humanity achieved a technological peak, before a widespread revolt of sentient machines.",
  "Stasis fields are ancient technological remnants used to indefinitely freeze objects or people in time, sometimes over thousands of years.",
  "A Relic in the Imperium is often a centuries-old piece of equipment, maintained with obsessive, near-religious fervor by the Mechanicus.",
  "Archaeotech refers to technology recovered from the Golden Age, often so advanced that the Mechanicus cannot replicate or fully understand it.",
  "The standard state of the galaxy is one of Total War, where the Imperium is constantly fighting on thousands of fronts against countless enemies.",
  "The Slaughter is the ultimate goal of the World Eaters, the Chaos Space Marines of Khorne, whose only purpose is an endless, bloody rampage.",
  "The Fallen are the rogue, non-Chaos loyalist members of the Dark Angels Legion who were separated by a Warp storm during the Heresy.",
  "The Harlequins are mysterious, theatrical Eldar followers of the Laughing God, Cegorach, who dance between the realms of the living and the dead.",
  "Ambulls are massive, subterranean, burrowing xenos creatures often utilized as heavy labor or combatants on frontier worlds.",
  "The Lizardmen from the fantasy world are hinted to be a related species to the Slann, ancient, powerful psychic toad-like beings who may have shaped the galaxy.",
  "The Squats, or Leagues of Votann, were a distinct, technologically advanced human subspecies who were believed to be consumed by the Tyranids, but have recently returned.",
  "The Yu'vath were an ancient, horrifying species that created the sinister, flesh-warping artifacts of the Dark Mechanicus.",
  "The Q'orl are a race of insectoid beekeepers who build incredible structures from wax and honey, who fought the Imperium during the Sabbat Worlds Crusade.",
  "The Lesser Daemon of the Plague God Nurgle, a Nurgling, is a diminutive, giggling miniature of its patron deity, spreading joy and disease.",
  "The Gretchin, or Grots, are the subservient, cowardly, but often surprisingly ingenious smaller cousins of the Orks, used as expendable labor and cannon fodder.",
  "For one moment, on the world of Sanctuary 101, a single, ordinary Guardsman successfully killed a Daemon Prince of Chaos with a well-placed grenade.",
  "The Great Work is the name given to the Emperor's failed project to create a safe, stable passage into the Webway for humanity, bypassing the Warp.",
  "The Planet of the Sorcerers is the Thousand Sons' home world within the Eye of Terror, a temporal paradox where time flows inconsistently.",
  "Despite all the terror, the vast majority of human life in the Imperium is a repetitive, soul-crushing toil, with every individual completely insignificant to the grand, galactic conflict.",
  "The Slaugth are horrific, maggot-men xenos who infiltrate human society to feast on the dead and decay.",
  "The two Lost Primarchs were excised from all Imperial records following an unknown tragedy and are now only mentioned in cryptic, fear-laden whispers.",
  "Lion El'Jonson, Primarch of the Dark Angels, has recently returned from a 10,000-year slumber, now awake and leading his confused Chapter into a new age.",
  "Leman Russ, the Wolf Lord, left the Imperium seeking a cure for the Emperor's injuries, vowing to return for the Final Battle at the End Times.",
  "Corvus Corax, the shadowy Primarch of the Raven Guard, was so horrified by the Horus Heresy that he entered the Eye of Terror to pursue and execute his traitorous brothers.",
  "Vulkan, the compassionate Primarch of the Salamanders, is an Perpetual, meaning he can regenerate from even the most grievous and fatal wounds.",
  "Jaghatai Khan, the master of hit-and-run warfare for the White Scars, vanished chasing Dark Eldar deep into the labyrinthine Webway.",
  "Ferrus Manus, the Gorgon of the Iron Hands, had hands sheathed in self-replicating liquid metal that he regarded as tools, not limbs.",
  "Sanguinius, the winged Primarch of the Blood Angels, died fighting Horus above Terra, forever crippling the forces of Chaos.",
  "Rogal Dorn, the stalwart Primarch of the Imperial Fists, was believed slain in the wreckage of a Chaos cruiser, though his hand was the only recovered remnant.",
