  "Konrad Curze, the prophetic Night Haunter, foresaw his own death and allowed an Imperial assassin to kill him, seeing it as the only just outcome of his life.",
  "Angron, the Primarch of the World Eaters, was forced into gladiator servitude on his homeworld, where he was implanted with the savage Butcher's Nails.",
  "Fulgrim, Primarch of the Emperor's Children, personally slew his brother Ferrus Manus and offered his head to Slaanesh.",
  "Mortarion, the Death Lord, rebelled due to his hatred of psychic powers and has since become the bloated, plague-ridden Daemon Primarch of the Death Guard.",
  "The Thunder Warriors were the Emperor's proto-Astartes, purged by the Custodes and the first Space Marines at the dawn of the Imperium.",
  "The Primarch Project was secretly overseen by the Emperor and the Mechanicum's most brilliant minds deep beneath the Himalayans on Terra.",
  "Each loyalist Primarch had a unique relationship with the Emperor, ranging from Dorn's unflinching obedience to Leman Russ's playful belligerence.",
  "The Emperor originally intended for the Primarchs to lead humanity into a new age of science, not endless religious warfare.",
  "The infant Primarchs were scattered across the galaxy by the machinations of the Chaos Gods, each landing on a unique world that shaped his destiny.",
  "The Custodes' primary task is the silent, unending vigil over the decaying body of the Emperor on the Golden Throne.",
  "The Terran Unification Wars were a brutal series of conflicts waged by the Emperor to bring the disparate, techno-barbaric clans of Old Terra under his rule.",
  "The Emperor’s psychic might is so vast that his dreams and thoughts occasionally manifest as minor, fleeting Warp entities.",
  "Malcador the Sigillite was the Emperor’s most trusted human confidante, who sat upon the Golden Throne in the Emperor’s stead during the final battle with Horus.",
