  "Tyranids adapt so rapidly that a fleet invading a new galaxy often encounters defenses that are wholly ineffective against the next wave.",
  "Rippers are the smallest Tyranid organisms, overwhelming prey with sheer numbers and stripping bodies clean of biomass.",
  "The Genestealers' Kiss is the process by which a Genestealer infects a host, implanting its genetic material and making the victim subservient to the cult.",
  "The Patriarch is the founder of a Genestealer Cult, a massive, powerful Genestealer who serves as the focus of the cult's psychic mind.",
  "The Broodlord is a highly evolved, physically imposing Genestealer that leads the vanguard of a Genestealer Cult in battle.",
  "The Aeldari rely on Aspect Warriors, specialized soldiers who dedicate their entire lives to a single martial path, such as the swooping Swooping Hawks.",
  "Wraithbone is the psychic, solidified substance that forms the basis of all Eldar technology, which can be shaped by their mind.",
  "The Spirit Stones worn by the Eldar contain their souls, protecting them from the immediate, hungry grasp of Slaanesh upon death.",
  "The Ynnari are a relatively new faction of Eldar who worship Yvraine, the prophet of the nascent death god Ynnead, hoping to defeat Slaanesh.",
  "The Striking Scorpions are Eldar Aspect Warriors who excel at close-quarters combat, equipped with the chain-bladed Scorpion Chainsword.",
  "The Dark Reapers are heavy weapons Aspect Warriors who use terrifying missile launchers to inflict massive damage from afar.",
  "Wytches are the gladiatorial combatants of the Dark Eldar, who fight in bloody arenas in Commorragh and derive life-extending pleasure from their acts.",
  "Kabalites are the primary, merciless raiders and soldiers of the Dark Eldar who lead the slave raids into real space.",
  "The Incubi are the elite, disciplined warriors of the Dark Eldar, known for their perfect combat mastery and terrifying strength.",
  "The Archon is the supremely ruthless leader of a Dark Eldar Kabal, who maintains power through constant murder, intrigue, and displays of cruelty.",
  "The T’au Fire Caste are the primary soldiers and combat specialists, known for their proficiency with railguns and pulse weaponry.",
  "The Ethereals are the philosophical and political leaders of the T'au, whose presence instills unwavering loyalty and devotion to the Greater Good.",
  "Vespid Stingwings are xenos auxiliaries of the T’au, noted for their airborne combat and specialized energy weapons.",
  "Kroot Shapers are the leaders of their kind, who strategically choose which enemies the Kroot should consume to best adapt their genetics.",
  "Railguns are the devastating primary weapon of the T'au, capable of punching through the thickest armor with massive kinetic force.",
  "Necron Overlords are the most senior and powerful Necrons, obsessed with regaining their ancient glory and enslaving the other races.",
  "Necron Warriors are the basic foot soldiers, mindless robots who march in lockstep and self-repair thanks to their Reanimation Protocols.",
  "The Tomb Stalker is a terrifying, massive Necron construct that tunnels beneath the surface to ambush foes with multiple legs and death rays.",
  "Flayed Ones are Necrons consumed by a horrific mental disease that drives them to flay their foes and wear the skin as trophies.",
  "The Triarch Praetorians are the self-appointed guardians of Necron dynastic traditions, who often operate outside the direct control of any Overlord.",
  "Gauss Flayers are the standard weapons of Necron infantry, disintegrating targets on a molecular level.",
  "The Stompa is an Ork's massive, lumbering walking war machine, often armed with grossly oversized and unreliable weaponry.",
