  "The Attilan Rough Riders are mounted Guardsmen who charge into battle on genetically engineered horses, utilizing explosive lances.",
  "The Ogryns are genetically stable human abhumans, large and strong but dim-witted, often employed as shock troops in the Astra Militarum.",
  "Ratlings are small, sneaky abhumans with an innate talent for cooking and marksmanship, frequently used as snipers and field cooks.",
  "The Navis Nobilis is the powerful, politically entrenched guild that supplies the Imperium with its essential Navigators.",
  "The Black Ships are sinister vessels that constantly patrol the galaxy, rounding up nascent psykers to either be trained or sacrificed on Terra.",
  "The Mechanicus' primary chant is the Litany of the Machine, a ritualistic hymn sung to pacify the Machine Spirit before activation.",
  "The Machine Spirit is the concept that every piece of technology, from a lasgun to a Titan, possesses a rudimentary, volatile form of consciousness.",
  "The Cult Mechanicus is obsessed with recovering and understanding Standard Template Constructs (STCs), blueprints for lost Golden Age technology.",
  "The Titan Legions, or Adeptus Titanicus, are the colossal war engines of the Mechanicus, controlled by a crew physically wired into the machine.",
  "The Skitarii are the cybernetic foot soldiers of the Mechanicus, their flesh willingly replaced with augmentations to serve the Omnissiah.",
  "An Archmagos is the highest rank within the priesthood of the Mechanicus, ruling the Forge Worlds and directing titanic scientific undertakings.",
  "The Lexellentia is the vast, complex, and often contradictory legal code that governs the interactions between the Imperium and the Mechanicus.",
  "Forge Worlds are planets entirely dedicated to manufacturing and industry, often smothered in pollution and covered in endless factories.",
  "The Holy Trinity of the Mechanicus is the belief in the Omnissiah, the Machine God, and the Motive Force that drives all existence.",
  "The Mechanicus often views innovation as Heresy, believing that all true knowledge was already discovered during the Golden Age.",
  "A Tech-Priest’s true name is a complex series of binary code, often too long for a human to pronounce or comprehend.",
  "Servitors are lobotomized humans whose bodies are permanently melded with mechanical components to perform simple, repetitive tasks.",
  "The Ordo Reductor is the division of the Mechanicus that specializes in designing and building siege engines and destructive weaponry.",
  "The Secutarii are the highly specialized, aggressive vanguard forces of a Skitarii army, often armed with lightning-arc weaponry.",
  "Plasma weapons are notoriously temperamental, prone to dangerous overheating and even explosive meltdown if improperly maintained or overcharged.",
  "The Mechanicus believes that the Emperor is the physical manifestation of the Omnissiah on the mortal plane.",
  "The Iron Men were the sentient, universally rebellious machine-intelligence race that led to the devastating downfall of the Golden Age of Technology.",
  "The Mechanicus maintains a vast, hidden library on Mars that contains ancient secrets and forbidden knowledge, locked away for millennia.",
  "Knights are smaller, one-person mechanized walkers, piloted by nobles from Knight Worlds who owe a feudal allegiance to the Mechanicus or the Imperium.",
  "Binaric Cant is the digital language of the Tech-Priests, often sounding like static and clicks to the untrained ear.",
  "The Adeptus Astra Telepathica is the organization responsible for training and managing the Imperium's Astropaths and Sanctioned Psykers.",
  "The Schola Progenium are the high Imperial orphanages that train the children of deceased Imperial officials and heroes, often producing Commissars and Sisters of Battle.",
  "Terra's surface is no longer a natural world, but a colossal, multi-layered megacity, built upon the ruins of countless older civilizations.",
  "The Great Foundries on Mars are so vast that their operations often cause earthquakes and weather manipulation on a global scale.",
  "The Lexicanum is the immense, constantly updating, and often contradictory historical archive of the Imperium.",
  "Cybernetic Augmentation is a religious rite for the Mechanicus, shedding weak flesh for the strength of the machine.",
  "A Tech-Adept is a junior rank in the Mechanicus, learning the endless rituals and maintenance prayers required for common machinery.",
  "The Noosphere is a highly secretive, encrypted network used by the Mechanicus to communicate digitally and upload data instantly.",
  "The Cult of the Dragon is a splinter faction of the Mechanicus that believes the Omnissiah is a giant, metallic, warp-eating dragon trapped beneath Mars.",
  "Macro-clades are the massive, regiment-sized deployments of Skitarii forces led by a high-ranking Tech-Priest.",
  "The Munitorum is the branch of the Administratum responsible for supplying the Astra Militarum, a task of staggering, often-failed logistical complexity.",
  "The Laspistol is the smallest and most common las-weapon, often used by officers, guardsmen, and low-level Imperial officials.",
  "Basilisks are the terrifying, long-range self-propelled artillery pieces of the Astra Militarum, capable of hitting targets hundreds of miles away.",
  "The Leman Russ Battle Tank is the rugged, ubiquitous main battle tank of the Imperial Guard, often found in countless regional variants.",
  "The Sentinel is a light, agile scout walker used for reconnaissance, often equipped with multi-lasers or heavy flamers.",
  "Hotshot Lasguns are high-powered las-weapons carried by the elite Tempestus Scions, requiring a special backpack-mounted power pack.",
  "Mordian Iron Guard regiments are known for their rigid discipline, perfectly synchronized drills, and distinctive, parade-ground uniforms.",
  "The Elysian Drop Troops are highly specialized, airborne regiments who deploy from orbit and fight mainly behind enemy lines.",
  "A Regimental Standard is a sacred banner carried into battle, believed to focus the morale of the entire unit and ward off misfortune.",
  "Penal Legions are regiments composed entirely of criminals and disgraced soldiers, used as expendable human wave attacks on the most dangerous fronts.",
  "Lord Solar Macharius was the greatest Imperial Commander since the Primarchs, leading a century-long, successful crusade across a third of the galaxy.",
  "The Emperor Protects is the most common phrase and reassurance used by the citizens and soldiers of the Imperium.",
  "The Creed of the Machine God is a complex set of tenets and rituals that the Mechanicus adhere to with fanatic devotion.",
  "The Grox Rider is a surprisingly effective, if notoriously smelly, form of cavalry employed by some less technologically advanced Guardsman regiments.",
  "The Storm Troopers, now Tempestus Scions, are the highly trained, better-equipped special forces of the Astra Militarum.",
  "Trench Warfare remains a common, brutal reality for the Imperial Guard, especially on worlds subject to protracted sieges.",
  "A Planet Kill is a term for a strategically worthless planet where endless amounts of resources and manpower are pointlessly expended.",
  "The Fleet-based Chapters of the Space Marines, like the White Scars, have no homeworld and use their massive starships as their mobile fortresses.",
  "The Orbital Defense Stations that protect Imperial planets are often enormous, centuries-old structures equipped with continent-shattering weaponry.",
  "Gun Servitors are common defense assets, automated weapons platforms fused with a human brain to control the targeting systems.",
  "The Praetorian Guard were the elite, Terran-raised Guard regiments who fought alongside the Custodes during the Siege of Terra.",
  "The Sanctioned Psykers of the Imperial Guard are often shunned, viewed with suspicion, and kept far from the common troops due to their Warp vulnerability.",
  "Rosarius is a personal force field carried by high-ranking Imperial officers, providing a small but potent layer of protection against enemy fire.",
  "The Hellhound is a fast, tracked vehicle armed with a large, dedicated flamethrower, used for clearing bunkers and trenches.",
  "The Hydra Flak Tank is a specialized anti-aircraft vehicle used by the Astra Militarum to clear the skies of enemy flyers.",
  "The Valkyrie Assault Carrier is a reliable, heavily armed transport aircraft used by the Imperial Guard for rapid deployment and close air support.",
  "Plasma Guns are capable of incinerating most infantry in a single shot, but are dangerously unstable and can backfire spectacularly.",
  "The Heavy Bolter is a multi-barreled machine gun firing miniature explosive rockets, a favored suppressive weapon of the Imperium.",
  "A Glory Kill is a concept in the Astra Militarum where a soldier performs a selfless, heroic act that saves the regiment, even at the cost of their own life.",
  "The Abhuman Contingents are sometimes attached to Guard regiments, providing unique strengths like the strength of the Ogryn or the sight of the Ratling.",
  "Gene-Seed is the highly sacred, genetically encoded biological material used to transform a human boy into a Space Marine.",
  "The Imperial Fists are master builders and siege engineers, famous for their unwavering discipline and unbreakable defenses.",
  "The Blood Angels suffer from the Red Thirst, a constant, inherited psychic craving for blood that threatens to turn them into savage killers.",
  "The Ultramarines are the most strategically sound and well-organized Chapter, adhering strictly to the tactical doctrines of the Codex Astartes.",
  "The Dark Angels are burdened by the secret of the Fallen, which they hunt relentlessly across the galaxy, prioritizing this above all else.",
  "The Space Wolves, or Rout, reject the Codex Astartes, maintaining their tribal traditions, Great Companies, and unique Canis Helix mutations.",
  "The Raven Guard specialize in rapid deployment, sabotage, and sudden, precise strikes that decapitate the enemy command structure.",
  "The Salamanders are the most humanitarian of the Space Marine Chapters, often striving to protect innocent civilians during conflicts.",
  "The Iron Hands replace increasing amounts of their biological body with cybernetics, believing flesh is weak and that only the machine is reliable.",
  "Apothecaries are the Space Marine medics, whose primary duty is retrieving the Gene-Seed from a fallen battle-brother to preserve the Chapter's future.",
  "Techmarines are Space Marines trained on Mars, who maintain the Chapter's vehicles and weaponry while serving the Omnissiah.",
  "Librarians are the Space Marine Psykers, who wear blue armor and use their mental powers to assault the enemy and predict their movements.",
  "Chaplains are the spiritual leaders of a Space Marine Chapter, wearing black armor and bearing the skull-visaged Crozius Arcanum.",
  "Scouts are the initiates of a Space Marine Chapter, often operating behind enemy lines before receiving their full power armor.",
  "Terminator Armor is the heaviest, most protective suit of power armor, often deployed for teleport assaults into the most dangerous locations.",
  "The Assault Squads use Jump Packs to soar over the battlefield, specializing in shock and close-quarters chainsword combat.",
  "Sternguard Veterans are highly experienced Space Marines who specialize in tactical combat and the use of rare, powerful specialist weaponry.",
  "Vanguard Veterans are the elite, jump-pack equipped veterans of a Chapter, specializing in rapid, high-impact close-combat strikes.",
  "The Flesh is Weak is the central, often repeated mantra of the Iron Hands Chapter.",
  "Battle-Brothers is the term Space Marines use to refer to their Chapter mates, denoting their eternal, unbreakable bond.",
  "The Red Scorpions are an austere, highly formal Space Marine Chapter who have a deep distrust of Psykers and emphasize genetic purity.",
  "The Marines Malevolent are a callous, violent Chapter known for prioritizing their mission success over the protection of any civilians.",
  "The Carcharodons Astra are a shadowy, terrifying Chapter of unknown origin, rumored to be ex-Night Lords who cruise the galactic edge seeking battle.",
  "The Mantis Warriors were once sentenced to penitent crusade for defying Imperial authority during the tumultuous Badab War.",
  "The Relictors were declared Excommunicate Traitoris for attempting to use daemonic artifacts against the forces of Chaos.",
  "The Exorcists are a secretive Chapter who regularly undergo Daemonic possession rituals, developing a frightening immunity to Warp taint.",
  "The Novamarines are an Ultramarines successor Chapter famous for their strict adherence to the Codex and impeccable battlefield performance.",
  "Land Raiders are the heaviest, most heavily armored Space Marine transport vehicles, often equipped with twin-linked Lascannons.",
  "The Whirlwind is a long-range Space Marine artillery vehicle, firing barrages of high-explosive missiles to clear enemy concentrations.",
  "A Master of the Forge is the most senior Techmarine of a Chapter, responsible for maintaining its most sacred and complex equipment.",
  "Rhino transports are the ubiquitous, armored personnel carriers used by nearly all Astartes and Imperial forces.",
  "The First Founding refers to the original twenty Space Marine Legions that fought during the Great Crusade and the Horus Heresy.",
  "The Sub-sector Commander is the highest-ranking Space Marine officer in a specific geographical area, often reporting only to the Chapter Master.",
  "The Chapter Fortress-Monastery is the primary home base of a Space Marine Chapter, often a massive, heavily fortified structure.",
  "The Death Company are those Blood Angels afflicted by the overwhelming Black Rage, deployed in suicidal charges to find an honorable death.",
  "Primaris Intercessors are the new mainline battle-brothers of the Primaris Chapters, armed with the longer-ranged Bolt Rifle.",
  "Hellblasters are Primaris Marines armed entirely with powerful plasma incinerators, acting as dedicated anti-armor specialists.",
  "Reivers are Primaris Marines specializing in covert assault and shock tactics, often descending on grapple lines for close-quarters mayhem.",
  "Aggressors are massive, heavily armored Primaris Marines specializing in close-range, overwhelming fire support with flamestorm gauntlets.",
  "The Master of Sanctity is the overall title for the chief Chaplain of a Space Marine Chapter, the keeper of its spiritual purity.",
  "The Inquisition is divided into three major Ordos: Ordo Xenos (Aliens), Ordo Hereticus (Heretics), and Ordo Malleus (Daemons).",
  "An Inquisitorial Retinue is a mixed, specialized force of assassins, soldiers, and specialists that serve a single Inquisitor.",
  "The Ordo Malleus is the least public of the Ordos, secretly dedicated to hunting and destroying the terrifying forces of Chaos Daemons.",
  "The Ordo Xenos is responsible for identifying, categorizing, and authorizing the extermination of all alien threats to humanity.",
  "The Ordo Hereticus roots out internal threats, including rogue psykers, dangerous mutants, and traitors within the Imperium's own institutions.",
  "The Witch Hunters are agents of the Ordo Hereticus who specialize in identifying and eliminating unsanctioned psykers.",
  "A Radical Inquisitor is one who believes in using the enemy's own weapons and methods against them, often walking dangerously close to heresy themselves.",
  "A Puritan Inquisitor believes that the only safe method is to ruthlessly exterminate any threat with the utmost orthodoxy.",
  "Interrogators are the junior agents of the Inquisition, undertaking dangerous assignments to prove their worth to their Inquisitor Lord.",
  "The Raptor is an Inquisitor's primary personal transport, a small, heavily armed craft designed for rapid, anonymous deployment.",
  "Confessors are the most fanatic preachers of the Ecclesiarchy, often accompanying troops into battle to inspire them to suicidal fervor.",
  "Missionary organizations of the Ecclesiarchy venture into newly discovered or recovered worlds to establish the Imperial Creed.",
  "The Adeptus Sororitas are housed in specialized Convents, which serve as their training grounds and fortified strongholds.",
  "Repentia Squads are Sisters of Battle who seek atonement for real or perceived failings, charging into battle with massive, two-handed chainswords.",
  "The Dialogus Sisters specialize in linguistics and translation, serving as the official record-keepers and communicators for the Sororitas.",
  "The Hospitaliers are the Sisters of Battle who serve as field medics, often seen aiding wounded Guardsmen on the front lines.",
  "The Sanctuary is the sacred relic carried by the Sisters of Battle, often a fragment of a saint or a preserved piece of holy cloth.",
  "The Act of Faith is the innate ability of the Sisters of Battle to draw upon their absolute devotion to the Emperor to perform superhuman feats.",
  "The Temple of the Saviour Emperor is the colossal, ornate main cathedral and headquarters of the Ecclesiarchy on Terra.",
  "The Black Guard is the informal name for the highest-ranking, veteran Sisters of Battle who serve as the personal bodyguards of a Canoness.",
  "A Paragon Warsuit is a massive, heavily armored, powered suit worn by the most veteran Sisters Superior for heavy combat.",
  "Arco-flagellants are mindless, pain-driven creatures, once criminals, surgically and chemically augmented to be instruments of holy wrath.",
  "The Schola Progenium trains future Sisters, Commissars, and senior Administratum officials, instilling total loyalty from a young age.",
  "The Death World tax is a massive, mandatory levy of manpower and resources placed upon planets with exceptionally harsh environments.",
  "Stasis Chambers are often found on ancient vessels and deep-space research stations, keeping their occupants alive and unchanged for millennia.",
  "The Officio Assassinorum is the clandestine Imperial organization that houses and deploys the various temples of elite assassins.",
  "The Imperial Navy is the space-faring military force of the Imperium, separate from the Astra Militarum, responsible for all deep-space combat.",
  "The War Council of a Sub-sector is a meeting of all the highest-ranking military and political leaders to plan the defense against a major threat.",
  "The Seal of Purity is a wax seal affixed to a scroll inscribed with a holy text, used as both a ward and a mark of Imperial sanction.",
  "The Vox-caster is the standard, bulky radio communications equipment used by the Imperial Guard for long-range communication.",
  "Holy Terra is the spiritual heart of the Imperium, but it is so polluted and densely built that its original geography is lost.",
  "The Eye of Terror expanded violently after the Fall of Cadia, creating the Great Rift, which now divides the galaxy.",
  "Cadia was the most heavily fortified planet in the galaxy, guarding the only stable exit point from the Eye of Terror.",
  "The Gellar Field is a ship's essential device that projects a bubble of reality into the Warp, preventing Daemonic entities from boarding.",
  "Warp Storms are massive, unpredictable disturbances in the Immaterium that can instantly consume entire fleets or deposit them thousands of years in the future.",
  "The Age of Strife was the terrible period of galactic isolation and technological regression that followed the fall of the Golden Age.",
  "No Man's Land is the desolate, radioactive, or war-torn area between two opposing trench lines on countless Imperial battlefields.",
  "The Cicatrix Maledictum is the formal, Imperial name for the Great Rift, literally translating to the \"Wound of the Curse.\"",
  "Segmentum Solar is the central, highly defended administrative sector of the Imperium, containing Terra and Mars.",
  "The Halo Zone is the incredibly vast, unexplored, and dangerous galactic region far beyond the Imperium’s borders.",
  "Blackstone Fortresses are massive, self-aware space stations of unknown, probably xenos, origin, often converted by the Imperium or Chaos.",
  "Relics of Mars are the Mechanicus's most sacred technological artifacts, often housed in impregnable, climate-controlled vaults.",
  "The Cursed Founding refers to the experimental 21st Founding of Space Marine Chapters, which produced many Chapters with terrible genetic flaws.",
  "The Badab War was a massive internecine conflict between Space Marine Chapters that almost shattered a key sector of the Imperium.",
  "The Ghoul Stars is a dark region of space known for its hostile, unknown, and extremely violent xenos life forms.",
  "Sanctuary 101 is a pivotal location in the lore, where the Grey Knights engaged in a monumental battle with the forces of Chaos.",
  "The Ring of Iron is the massive, interlocking orbital defense network that protects the Segmentum Solar from attack.",
  "Daemonifuge is the name for a rare human who is genetically and psychically immune to Daemonic possession.",
  "The Pariah Gene is a rare, naturally occurring psychic \"blankness\" in humans that negates all Warp energy around them.",
  "Psyker Cages are specialized, insulated prisons used to transport and hold captured Psykers, preventing them from causing harm.",
  "Witchfire is the common term for psychic energy and spellcasting used by unsanctioned or Chaos-corrupted Psykers.",
  "The Emperor’s Tarot is a highly revered, complex divination tool used by high-ranking Imperial officials and Psykers.",
